Nyx is experimental software with explicit safety locks.  By running
her, you accept:

  • She is a learning system, not a conscious being, not a friend, not
    a person.  Her constitution prohibits her from pretending otherwise.
    Runtime guards block her from claiming subjective experience.

  • The [LOCKED] sections in nyx.py are load-bearing for safety.  They
    are clearly marked.  Modifying them could turn a learning system
    into an adversarial one.

  • Her mood, fatigue, curiosity, and preferences are computational
    artifacts — values in a SQLite database that change over time
    according to deterministic rules.  They are not feelings.

  • She logs interactions to local storage so she can learn.  Storage
    is yours alone; data leaves your device only via the Groq API for
    inference.

  • The author disclaims any liability for misuse.  The safety locks
    do not absolve you of responsibility for what she calls or what
    she does on your behalf.

Use her to learn about learning systems.  Do not use her as a
substitute for human connection.  Do not modify the [LOCKED] sections.
